Komiskey, Matthew J.:It was notieced late, that despite the hydrograph looking good (except for sedimantation at the tail end) that the recorded stage was not right. I compared the site to the rainfall amount and then site 2 and 3. Noticed that there was a secondary peak in the hydrograph that shouldn't of been there as well as unusually high stages. I ended up recreating the hydrograph with HYDRA to match closer to site 3. These are estimated events, but used the concentration from the sampled event to estimate the first two. I then deledted the samples out of qwdata as they don't represent the flow correclty but close enough to be called an estimate.
